        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 8 at 6:26PM CDT by NWS Huntsville AL</headline>
        <description>At 625 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Grant, or 7 miles north of Guntersville, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 40-50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Grant, Langston, Columbus City, Lake Guntersville St Park,
Guntersville, and Scottsboro.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM CDT for
north central and northeastern Alabama.</instruction>
